Defendant in custody.
The State moves to delete the repeater enhancer on both counts in 14 CF 539.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 1, deliver heroin.  Convicted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge in count 2, deliver heroin.  Convicted.
The Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five and one half (5.5) years.  That is two and one half (2.5) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, on each count concurrent, but consecutive to the sentence imposed on 10 CF 309.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) reimburse the Metro Drug Unit $60.00 for buy money on 14 CF 463,  joint and several with Stephanie Nething and $300.00 buy money on 14 CF 539;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Maintain fulltime employment;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety.
